Irish born Kim Carroll is a 2009
 Sundance Composer fellow and was awarded 'Gold medal of excellence' for the music he wrote for the thriller 'The Colony' at the 2008 Park City Film Music festival in Utah. He co-wrote the music for the film 'The Uninvited' with Harry Gregson-Williams (Shrek, Man on Fire, Narnia), has written music for RTE's 'PrimeTime', HBO's Addiction, NBC's Crossing Jordan, CBS ColdCase, VH1's Celebrity Fit Club, and Fox Sports. In addition, Carroll wrote the music for the feature-length documentary films "Survival of the Wildebeest" and the Sundance feature "The Horse Boy" w/ Lili Haydn. His latest scores were for the crime drama 'Across the Line (The Exodus of Charlie Wright)' starring Aidan Quinn, Andy Garcia, and Gina Gershon, and the drama/comedy "Congratulations".
 
 Carroll's music credits include Sinead O' Connor, Train, Paul Buchanan/Blue Nile, and Gary Jules (#1 UK hit with the song 'Mad World' from the film Donnie Darko). He can also be heard on the soundtracks for The Town, Gone,Baby,Gone, The Chronicles of Narnia(Prince Caspian), Veronica Guerin, Domino, and The Rundown. He is currently co-writing an album of original music with Lisbeth Scott (vocalist on Munich, Narnia, Passion of the Christ) to be released early next year.

KARST is a collaboration of two electronic music producers coming from different backgrounds, living and working in Berlin. One is a musical mastermind with an instinct for remarkable, but sometimes weird use of harmonies and sounds. The other a media artist and VJ who explores the synesthetic linkage between sound and visuals, approaching the field of music production from the technological side, eager to create new sounds from found material as well as by using various software tools. together, they produce deep, sometimes even humourous tracks of a noisy lowFi quality, suitable for the dancefloor, given an open-minded audience, ironic references to various styles of electronic music provide a diversified listening experience.

TRiOKA are Nathan John, Tim Hartley and Marc Denton.
|
Having all worked as DJs for years around the UK and Europe, the three first worked together earlier this summer, collaborating on a promotional mix CD for Romp in Sheffield. After a few sessions in the studio and several hundred ideas for names TRiOKA formed and began work proper on producing their first track, Faience. Since then they have established themselves at several residencies in Manchester, played numerous guest slots aross the UK and have continued to work on creating their own studio sound.
|
Feel free to post comments (positive or negative) about tracks or mixes on soundcloud. Most of the tracks are in a constant state of tinkering so any advice is always appreciated. 
|
Cheers

[Michigander / FXHE / Planet-E ]
As the world watches the renaissance and revival of Detroit, it listens for the sound of those carrying the torch of authentic Motor City-born techno into the future. Brian Kage is one of those innovators leading Detroit’s electronic music forward into the musical zeitgeist of change and revolution. 

Kage was recently crowned one of DJ magazine’s “10 Detroit Producers Keeping the Sound of the Motor City Alive.”

Detroit born-and-raised Kage co-founded record label Beretta Music, through which he mentored and helped shape the careers of many internationally respected DJs and producers.  Kage has also released well-received music on Omar S’s record label FXHE, Carl Craig’s Planet-E, Steve Bug’s PokerFlat, Rob Modell’s Echospace, and many more. Kage’s “DetroitLuv” record was featured and played on BBC Radio 1’s Essential Mix by Richie Hawtin and Ricardo Villalobos.

Kage’s “The Arc EP,” released on his own Michigander label, pays tribute to Detroit with its uplifting melodic techno style. “The Arc EP” was also featured and praised on Resident Advisor’s “New Tracks” list. Additionally, DJ magazine praised his collaboration with vocalist James Garcia, ‘Shut Your Eyes’, as “one of 2015’s best house tracks.” 

When he’s not working on his own music, Brian is working alongside local and international acts to mix, master and engineer their music with “KageMastering.” 

A vital part of Detroit’s rich techno history, Brian Kage is one of the artists and producers providing the score for the Motor City’s continuing rebirth. This is the sound of the future. This is Brian Kage.

Ericson Silva has always had his biggest passion in music. He began experiencing various instruments since he was a kid, when he started his studies, becoming a multi-instrumentalist with classical graduation. In 1998, already experienced in music and aware of the demand for commercial tracks in the world of advertising, had his first contact with the electronic scene. That’s when Ericson discovers his true punch. From there to here, he combines formal knowledge and his main influences – original brazilian popular music and 90’s international music - to compose and produce with competence and strong personality. His productions always aim for the sample-free melodic originality, and can be classified in genres: eletrofunk, hip-hop, trip-hop, lounge, house, progressive-house and techno.
My dj-duo: http://snake-n-tiger.de/.

Band names can be big. They can be clever. Or they can even be shit. But Dirty Rock & Roll do what it says on the tin. And then crush the tin so hard your ears start to bleed.

Formed from the ashes of North East noiseniks Baby Rattlesnakes, DRnR fuse punk, pop, metal and madness to deliver the best live shows around. They’re loud and very proud. They punch above their weight. And they’re well worth the wait.

Singer Adam found fame fronting the dearly departed Rattlesnakes for three years - supporting the likes of Electric Eel Shock, Quireboys and Tokyo Dragons. But the former basketball pro was always happiest crunching up Foos-style riffs with his rumbling vocals. In fact classic rock was never his cup of tea, so forming DRnR was the natural move for one of the region’s most imposing musos.

Surrounding himself with a rhythm section tighter than Metallica’s band security, Adam unearthed a killer combo. And if you don’t believe the hype then don’t tell Lee (bass) and Steve (drums). They’ll kick your arse from here to Blyth and back. Really. Tattooed millionaire Lee might look skinner than a lamppost but he rattles out some heavy shit. And if tub thumper Steve doesn’t cause his battered kit to collapse then it’s just not a DRnR gig.

The New Year means a new focus for one of Tyneside’s best kept secrets. In 2009 expect new tunes, a new attitude and even a new album. Expect DRnR to take it to the next level. Or demand a refund.

Streams of Europe was initially the code name of a sound and game design experiment. The idea was to create a soundtrack first, then build a video game upon it. Several albums and live sessions later, it appeared music had become a bit more than just a soundtrack.

The imaginary world at the origin of the project started to take form around 1994, as a pen & paper role-playing game. Many changes occured through the years, and many other media were tried. The musical aspect only emerged in the end of 2007. It’s meant to describe the horrors and wonders of Europe, after the Rain.

Streams of Europe evolved to a multimedia collective in the beginning of 2009. They’re currently focused on the development of the game. It seems like music is still too important to be simply put on hold, though.

JDSoundworx
Los Angeles, CA, Melbourne, Sydney, Edinburgh and London- JDSoundworx has announced a new album, "4tune8" Following the recent success of his album "ME GENERATION" along with its lead single, "Yeh! it's all about You"

"4TUNE8" is a crisp, and energetic piece of Raw Rock that finds Delaney with all the knives in his arsenal of skills sharpened to their finest edge. From its mingling of rock textures and sleek pop melodies to its fusion of smarts and catchiness, The lead single "Stand and Deliver" is an on-target introduction to Delaney and the JDSoundworx studio in Melbourne Australia.

JDSoundworx is Delaney's recording studio whose primary focus is the creation and production of music for placement in film and television and for other artists needing songs in the rock and pop fields. JDSoundworx, thanks to J Delaney's songwriting and production talents, is ever growing in its reputation as a source of songs that are geared to commercial requirements without loss of substance and staying power.

Recently, Delaney partnered with pacintmusic.com, the premier A&R firms based out of Los Angeles, CA, to help make even further inroads into the entertainment industry.
The forthcoming "4TUNE8" album and songs like "STAND AND DELIVER DUB-DANCE" are his calling cards and the best advocate a songwriter/producer could offer. Delaney's songs are audio revelations, with crystal clarity in the production of bright, vivacious, hooky pop rock bites.
Delaney is versatile behind the mixing boards, in the recording process and as a songwriter. He's just at home crafting retro-minded 70s rock to the pop flare of the new millennium, not to mention the spectrum of styles in between. And he's always up for a challenge.

In 2009, Ohlala! is no longer just a party offering renowned international artists such as Sinden or Etienne de Crecy, but also an art collective consisting of various free electrons of the Norwegian scene wanting to offer something fresh and, above all, to move your ass. 
Ohlala! is not a club concept, but a family that encourages and promotes musical creation and party spirit - turned to the European scene.

Currently Ohlala! is composed of three artists: DJ Final, Vinter in Hollywood and IllStM. 

Vinter In Hollywood is an extremely prolific producer that has been listed and played constantly on NRK P3 since january this year. He also just signed to So French Records for is first EP, and prepare the single of Lene Alexandra. Full of energy, Vinter plays live with his sampler, keyboard, mic and computer. Armed by sharp riff, vocoder voice and groovy beats, he surely will get the crowd to jump. 
www.myspace.com/vinterhollywood

IllStM is a french artist based in Norway and the founder of the Ohlala! collective. He is a saxophonist, producer and DJ. He met the electronic music in the early 90s with the first free parties of Spiral Tribe and in clubs with Laurent Garnier and Scan X. Armed with his laptop and his controller, he will play, without compromise, what can be caracterized as something in between a DJ set and live set, a powerfull electro house with one objectif: make you sweat!
www.myspace.com/illstmspace

After destroying pretty much every DJ in Europe in DJ battles, he is now set on destroying every dancefloor with electro, bmore, juke and a bunch of turntable trickery.

Homebelly has been making music in one form or another since he has been able to control his hand to eye coordination and bang his toys together. 
Over the years these toys have progressed from a bucket and spade in the sand pit, to guitars, synths, computers and microphones. 
Right now my primary tools are a mac book pro and ableton live/logic 8. I feed this combination sounds I have made with guitars, basses, synths and other sounds i have found while trawling the inter-web.
Primarily my motivation is to have fun and explore sound and sound design.

Comments are always welcome. especially in regards song arrangement, an area i suck at. 

Also.
I have no idea where i got any of the pictures i have used to tag my tracks.
I tend to grab any that i like while stumbling around the net with out keeping a record of where they have come from (does any one?)
So, if you recognize any, let me know and i will take them down or give credit where credit is due. 
No offense intended. 

Cheers, and thanks for stopping by.

K_Chico released his debut album "When I Was Young" in 2006 on the Teichmann- Brothers' "Festplatten" label. The release quickly found its way into the playlists of Electro luminaries such as GusGus, Ellen Alien, Chloe, Wighnomy Brothers, Munk etc. This in turn set off a chain of releases on Forcetracks, Rundlauf and the Bar25 label. As his touring schedule started to thicken and his career properly took off, K_Chico just walked away from it all.
Now - 5 years later - he is back with "Burn" - the first track from his new album, which will be released later on this year. The song comes with a visually intense music video produced and directed by the man himself. The production is based on the morphing effect and required hundreds of unique stills. The famous Champagne producers "Bollinger," who normally only sponsor James Bond movies, liked the test shots so much that they donated entire cases of their product to the crew. K_Chico is back!

The Geoff Lapp Trio'.....has been a cornerstone of the Montreal jazz scene since 1999. Extended gigs at many of the town's premiere night spots have established the group as a hot draw for aficionados in search of that heady space where soulful and cerebral fuse. Drawing upon a wide palette of jazz moods, 'The Geoff Lapp Trio' delivers a sound that is tasteful, innovative, and infectiously swinging.

The Geoff Lapp Trio is:Geoff Lapp (piano), Paul Johnston (bass), and Dave Laing (drums)

Geoff Lapp
 
Born in Montreal in 1953, Geoff Lapp was trained in the classical tradition and studied at McGill University under widely respected jazz pianist Art Maiste. During the early years of his career, he gained experience in the pop music world touring with the likes of Michel Pagliaro. From the early '80s onwards, he devoted himself fully to the jazz idiom. As one of Canada’s most accomplished pianists/composers, Geoff Lapp became a sought-after accompanist for a host of top Canadian performers.
 
In addition to his own trio work, Geoff has performed and/or recorded with renowned jazzmen such as Paquito d’Rivera, Don Menza, Richie Cole, Bob Mover, Sonny Fortune, and Slide Hampton, among others. He has also performed extensively in festivals and clubs worldwide. At home in Quebec, he is a mainstay on the vibrant jazz scene, and has performed with a panoply of hot local luminaries.

Reviews/Blurbs

""...has much to offer the jazz world.” ejazznews.com John Gilbert 4 Stars
"...a revelation: generously proportioned,understated, with moments of surprising audacity. The kind of jazz you didn’t think anyone was playing anymore." Macleans Paul Wells Dec 18, 2006

“...Melodic and swinging jazz piano from an underappreciated talent“ Salon.com

Sometimes things happen unexpectedly! Bimbo and Lemar met after a consequence of unpredictable massive underground events being held in old fabrics and warehouses in the northern suburbs of Berlin, but before that their ways appear to have winded to a direction that could hardly be followed!

In the early 90s Bimbo went to study in London and Lemar to New York. Their musical tastes then were severely influenced by artist like Aphex Twin, Carl Craig, Kevin Saunderson, Adonis, Derrick May and many others. The underground life captured their minds and the culture of the the dirty basements diversed their artistic horizons.

Bimbo felt the touch of vinyl for the first time at the end of 95and after that he couldnt just give it up. At that time Lemar was fascinated by the music production and bought a sampler and a drum machine and simply started experimenting with his brand new TB303.

They both began to organize independent underground parties and were appreciated by many. Bimbo and Lemar met in Berlin were they moved to live at the end of 90s. The dark artistic movement in Berlin absorbed their abilities and one day they met in a massive happening that was held in a beer fabric, just one day before it was supposed to be ruined. The fabric was actually ruined but Bimbo and Lemar were connected by the sound of violence which they both performed.

The DDP project was founded during their last tour in Ukraina, where the main aim was to help and redefine the nation's underground music, which makes Bimbo and Lemar one of the most conscientious artists on the scene. Thats simply how it all started!

O projeto MOR é desenvolvido por Guilherme Figueiredo, este mesmo que vos fala.

A história de minhas músicas é bem longa e bem intensa. Assim como minha própria existência (não é tão longa assim, se pensar bem..) Na verdade, “intensidade” é o modo utilizado para produzi-las, música e existência.

Muita energia psíquica (física também) gasta de forma sempre muito intensa. Experiências, diálogos reais e imaginários, fantasias, desejos, sonhos, frustrações, medos, enfim, tudo que faz parte de nosso dia-a-dia de estar sempre no limite da sanidade e a loucura.

Uma viagem ao inconsciente, a imagens, pessoas, situações, espiritualidade, ao mundo em si (a representação de um sonho em vigília, nada mais que a vida).

Buscando de maneira obsessiva seqüência de freqüências tão perfeitas em sua entonação e cores que não existem. Buscando algo mesmo sabendo que não existe. Mas buscando. Sempre buscando.

Enfim, é uma pira.

Desde o inicio aos últimos ajustes técnicos da música, cada segundo é “sublimado” conforme a temática, buscando causar sensações, pensamentos e até mesmo fantasias.

(Não deixa de ser um interessante “instrumento” de auto-análise. Surge cada história absurda e é interessante que acabo lidando com meus processos internos e externos – hmm, fugindo de alguns deles também, “transformando” em música...)

É um trabalho completamente eletrônico e computadorizado, sim.

Entretanto é, acima de tudo, um trabalho extremamente humano, espiritual e existencial.

Namastê!

Dub Elements y Venganza presentan: ELEMENTS OF VENGEANZE:
“EOV es un proyecto que venia incubandose desde tiempo atrás”. A finales de 2009 se le decide poner nombre y forma física, a lo que había sido un año de colaboraciones, tanto en su vertiente drum and bass como con la creación de un proyecto paralelo conjunto; UNABLE (http://www.myspace.com/unablespain).

No hace falta decir mucho acerca de estos artistas, Dub elements y Venganza, quienes por separado han tenido un largo recorrido en paralelo bajo la etiqueta de RESISTANCE, actuando en gran parte de las capitales Europeas: Londres, Munich, Dresden, Sofía, Madrid, Barcelona, Bucharest, Bratislava, Moscú o Rotterdam por citar algunas y los cuales han colocado su música en sellos tan influyentes como PRSPCT, OFFKEY o HABIT entre otros, ganándose el respeto y apoyo de artistas de la talla de PANACEA, RAIDEN, AUDIO, GEIN o MASHEEN.

En tan solo unos meses de existencia han conseguido firmar su primer EP/LP, el cual verá la luz en abril, con el conocido sello madrileño FILTHY SANCHEZ, para el cual nos traen 2 temas originales, así como varias colaboraciones sorpresa y un remix del mítico FUCKING de KALASHNIKOV para la versión en vinilo y 4 temas mas inéditos para la versión CD/Digital.

su gira de presentacion ya tiene confirmada la presencia en festivales de renombre como PRSPCT XL EDITION o VIÑAROCK, además de una gira Europea q no para de aumentar dia tras dia.

Dub Elements & Venganza introducing ELEMENTS OF VENGEANZE:
“EOV is a project that has been in development for a long time”. At the end of 2009 they decided to make it real and give it a name and entity, and a year of collaborations on all the aspects of music they write; both drum and bass and their side project UNABLE (http://www.myspace.com/unablespain).

It is not necessary to introduce these artists, Dub Elements and Vengeanze, who in their single careers have come a long way with their RESISTANCE label, playing in most of the main European city’s such as: London, Munich, Dresden, Sofia, Madrid, Barcelona, Bucharest, Bratislava, Moscow or Rotterdam just to mention some, and who have released their music on labels as influential as PRSPCT, OFFKEY and HABIT among others, getting supported by people like PANACEA, RAIDEN, AUDIO, GEIN and MASHEEN.

In only a few months they signed their first EP/digital LP, which will be released in April, with the infamous Spanish label FILTHY SANCHEZ, with two original songs, as well as some collabs and a remix of the mythical FUCKING from KALASHNIKOV for the vinyl version and 4 more original tunes for the cd/digital LP.

Their launch tour has confirmed dates in festivals such as PRSPCT XL EDITION o VIÑAROCK, besides a European tour that grows day by day.

East German transplant and current Los Angeles resident Hofhauser has always loved electronic music. There are not many emerging artists that study the music and pay attention to trends the way this budding DJ does.

When the wall came down in 1989, many underground clubs emerged from the rubble. In the early 90’s, clubs such as The Distillery in Leipzig became a hotbed for musical talent. It was here where Hofhauser got his start, swaying crowds back and forth until the wee hours of the morning. Back then it was house music reigning supreme. When asked recently what style of music he plays, Hofhauser responded with a smile: “I play funky minimal, groovy, deep, quirky electronica with a melodic edge.” 

His sets will take you on a journey into the minds eye. It will take you on an early morning trip through the rubble of east germany. it will take you where you want to go. Wherever “there” is.

Nesola lässt niemanden allein
      Max Herre setzt mit seinem Anfang des Jahres gegründeten Label Nesola auf beseelte Musik.
      Am Abend des 21. Aprils hatte Max Herre, vielen noch bekannt als Frontmann von Freundeskreis, gleich zwei Gründe zum Feiern: Zum einen den Labelstart von Nesola und dessen Deal mit Sony BMG/ Four Music, zum anderen um Mitternacht seinen Geburtstag. Es herrschte dichtes Gedränge im Berliner Jazz-Club A-Trane, als Herre seine Gäste zur Nesola Labelounge begrüßte. Darunter Fitz Braum, Geschätsführer Four Music, Tessy Schulz, Domestic Berlin Sony BMG, und André Mühlhausen, Sales Sony BMG, sowie Jürgen Vogel, der sich selbst als größten Nesola-Fan bezeichnete. „’Nesola’ ist esperanto und heißt ‚nicht allein’“, übersetzt Herre den Labelnamen. Und Nesola sei kein Alleingang. Er habe das Label mit seiner Frau Joy Denalane, Götz Gottschalk und Sophie Raml gegründet. Zu seinem Team in Berlin gehören Deirdre Laughton (Product Manager) Yvonne Njiké (Management) und Joys Schwester Doreen Denalane (Assistant). Mit im Boot sitzen auch Four Music, mit denen gemeinsam Marketing und Promotion durchgeführt wird, und Sony BMG, die den Vertrieb des Label übernehmen. „Mi Libro Abierto“ heißt das erste, im März veröffentlich¬te Album von Laura Lopez Castro auf Nesola. Für Juni ist die Veröffentlichun¬gen der Single „Let Go“ von Joy Denalane geplant, im August soll ihr Album folgen. Wann Herre selbst mit einer neuen Produktion aufwarten wird, hat er nicht verraten. „Ich freue mich sehr darüber, so außergewöhnliche Künstler auf dem Label zu haben, und finde, Laura gibt einen wunderbaren Ton für das vor, was wir mit Nesola vorhaben“, erzählt er.  Das Label stehe für Musik mit Seele und Künstler mit Charisma. Und davon konnten sich die Gäste an dem Abend überzeugen. 
      Eine zierliche Gestalt mit  krausen dunklen Haaren und blassem Gesicht betrat nach Herres Begrüßung die Bühne. Ein schüchternes „Hallo!“, dann begann die Musik. Ein leises, gefühlvolles Gitarrenintro erklang und Laura Lopez Castros Ausdruck verwandelte sich. Mit klagend erhobener und von Melancholie getränkter Stimme sang sie von der Vergänglichkeit der Schönheit, Dornen tragender Liebe und versiegenden Tränen, zuweilen getragen von einem wunderbar schwermütigen Celloklang. In einigen Liedern gesellte sich ein vorsichtig flüsterndes Trompetenspiel dazu. Alle Songs sind auch auf ihrer aktuellen CD „Mi Libro Abierto“ enthalten. Die Texte schreibt Castro überwiegend selbst. Ihr Produzent ist Don Philippe, der auch Gitarrist des Ensembles ist. Außerdem zum Ensemble gehören Cellistin Deanna Talens sowie Trompeter und Pianist Sebastian Studnitzky. Auf die eher wehmütigen Weisen von Castro folgte ein musikalischer Kontrapunkt: Mit ihrer kraftvollen Stimme und ihrer temperamentvollen Art riss Soulsängerin Joy Denalane die Gäste von Stühlen und Hockern und animierte zum mitsingen, als sie ihre neue Single „Let Go“ vorstellte. Am Klavier begleitet wurde sie von Lillo Scrimali. Denalane sei glücklich, wieder neue Songs singen zu dürfen, sagte sie. Und ihre Fans dürfen sich freuen, sie bald hören zu können.
      Max Herre hat dem „Musikmarkt“ vor der Labelounge in einem Email-Interview bereits einige Details zur Labelgründung berichtet. So erzählt er zur Namensgebung: „Wir hatten von Anfang an den Anspruch, Musik und Texte zu produzieren, in denen sich Menschen wieder finden, sie also nicht alleine zulassen.“ Nicht zuletzt wegen des 1999er Freundeskreis-Albums gebe es einen Bezug zu der Welt-Sprache Musik. Sie sei die universellste aller Sprachen. „Mit Laura López Castro und auch mit Joy Denanlanes haben wir bereits zwei internationale Produktionen auf Nesola. Am 1. Mai veröffentlichen wir Laura auch in Frankreich.“ 
      Die Gründung von Nesola resultiere aus einer sehr natürlichen Entwicklung der 10jährigen Zusammenarbeit mit Four Music, sagt Herre. „Ich hatte bei Four Music in den letzten Jahren de facto schon den Status eines A&Rs erworben. Mit Freundeskreis oder FK Allstars, unter anderem mit Gentleman, Afrob und Joy, konnte ich beweisen, dass ich ein Gefühl für musikalisches Talent habe und die Fähigkeit besitze, Musikern eine Plattform zu geben. Nesola ist nun auch geschäftlich die Konsequenz daraus.“ Das Unternehmen verstehe sich nicht als Platten-Label im klassischen Sinn. Vielmehr sei es eine Musikfirma, die alle Bereiche der Vermarktung von Musik abdecken möchte. Dazu gehörten zum Beispiel auch Management, Publishing und Merchandising. „An traditionellen Labelaufgaben übernehmen wir das A&R und Produkt Management.“ 
      Herre tue sich schwer, sich bei dem Label auf ein bestimmtes Genre festzulegen, erzählt er. Das Problem habe er auch schon mit seinen eigenen Projekten gehabt. „Und wenn Du Laura fragst, was für eine Musikrichtung sie macht, wird sie bestimmt antworten: ‚Irgendwas zwischen Bossa, Fado und Singer/ Songwriter.’“ Statt sich auf ein musikalisches Genre festzulegen, kommt es ihm vielmehr darauf an, Musik mit Seele auf eigenwilligen Alben zu veröffentlichen, die internationales Format haben. Über die aktuellen Pläne berichtet er: „Wir sind noch Mitten in der Kampagne von Lauras erster Veröffentlichung, für die wir ein Jahr Zeit eingeplant haben. Die Resonanz war überwältigend, und wir rechnen uns hier in Deutschland sowie auch international noch einiges aus. Dann kommt Joy Denalanes Album im August und eine Single vorab Mitte Juni. Damit sind wir für dieses Jahr wirklich ausgelastet. Und dann setzte ich mich auch wieder an was Neues, sobald ich Joys Produktion abgeschlossen habe.“
      An dem Abend der Labellounge wurden erst der offizielle Start des Labels und seine Künstler gefeiert, um Mitternacht bekam dann der Künstler, Produzent, A&R und Labelgründer Max Herre selbst ein Ständchen und eine Torte zu seinem 33. Geburtstag. Was er sich wünschte, als er die Kerzen ausblies, blieb sein Geheimnis.

Produkt was comprised of two individuals (MobiusB and MCQ6) and frequently collaborated with other artists ( Jim Phelps, Akisma, Crisis).

MobiusB (Bill Bendrot)- Originally from New Jersey, MobiusB escaped and attended college at Bostons Berklee College of music in 1992. Former guitarist for Jersey band 'Trademark' and Boston band 'Groove Tree' Mobius switched gears and has been in on the electronic scene since early 99 producing his own tracks and releasing them on his site MobiusB.com. In 2000 MobiusB started releasing new material with a much more produced and complete feel. Mobius started rising through the ranks of the multitude of talented New England area DJs and producers spinning his own unique blend of original and released acid breaks, progressive trance, nu skool and ambient as well as video art at such venues as the Exchange, Jose McIntyres, The International, Dimension, Paddy Burkes, The Middle East, The Sugar Shack, ManRay and Evos. Now with Produkt, Mobius brings live electronic drumming and percussion, bass, synth and sequencing and some of the DJ sensibilities and tools of the dance floor to the table as well as some technical wizardry and psychedelic visual artwork and film.


McQ6 (John McKusick)- Formerly known as Punasti, MCQ6 has been performing locally since 1988. Former front man of local bands October's Child and Paradox Lost. MCQ6 has studied briefly at Berklee College of Music for vocals and briefly under Mark Marquis for theory and guitar. Since the year 2000 he has teamed up with fellow band mate Mike Fun to produce material under the name Hypocycloid and then Produkt in 2002. During this time MCQ6 has developed his electronic musicianship and has currently added a guitar synthesizer to the list of midi triggers the band currently posesses. MCQ6 is a man of many hats. Playing guitar, bass, synthesizers, Keyboards, vocals, percussion, visual art direction, video editing, graphic and web design. MCQ6 currently plays bass and guitar for the Coretta Sellars band. A folk side project. MCQ6 has played the Sugar Shack, VOIX, The Grainery, Smithwick's, The Wallace Planetarium, The Lake Lodge, The Brew Locker, Club 490, Slatterys, Partner's Pub. the Renisance Cafe, Martha's Brewery Exchange, Sharky's, Fishtown Artspace, Sydney's, the Bernstein Bookstore, UMASS Lowell, Fitchburg State, ManRay in Cambridge and Evos in Lowell.

Formed in 1998, Canada's D-TRASH Records started as an online collective by members of CPUWAR and DJ RABIES as the beginnings of an international network of exciting and extreme electronic music artists. In 2000, the group formed into an official record label, headed by D-TRASH artist SCHIZOID, the label now coming forth with pressed CD releases for sale in stores; as well, continuing the practice of releases of full-length albums through the internet as MP3 for download. The label sprouted with artists based in many parts of the world, whose material was getting such acclaim and press from KERRANG, TERRORIZER, ROCK SOUND, and INDUSTRIAL NATION - In 2003 D-TRASH Records CDs were picked up for a North American distribution deal with infamous German label DIGITAL HARDCORE RECORDINGS through CAROLINE Distribution, as well as  many D-TRASH artists also appearing on the 3xCD DHR compilation "Don't Fuck With Us". To date in 2008, its 10th year of business, the label has put out 8 professionally pressed CDs and 1 DVD available in stores/distros worldwide and have released roughly 120 full length albums (with artwork) available for MP3 download on the http://www.dtrashrecords.com site.

lilak monoke is an experimental electronic music producer from berlin and can be reached at lilakmonokeättgmaildötcom ... 

lilak monoke produces music that is related to techno, funk, ambient music and game and movie soundtracks ... 

for the last years lilak monoke has been working on organic microtiming code and mathematical sequencing tools that are based on pattern language and prime numbers ... 

lilak monoke works mostly without DAW  and analog synths, vintage samplers and first take recordings ... 

lilak monoke is part of a larger place called the UNIVERSE, which is generally a good place but need lots of exploration because of its sheer size ...

Tres Colores Joe trae un pop/rock introspectivo desde Madrid, España. Este es su primer disco, completamente autoproducido, con 12 canciones que dan que pensar.

Aunque Tres Colores Joe hace todo desde Madrid, realmente es el fruto de las experiencias de tres personas que vienen de sitios diferentes. Mariana Middle-Tone, la voz de 3cJ, viene de Santiago de Chile. Carlos "The Hitman" Rodríguez, de Madrid, toca las guitarras. Alex León, Venezolano-Canario, ha producido el disco además de tocar la batería y los bajos.

Los temas fueron grabados y masterizados entre agosto del 2008 y enero del 2009 en los estudios ZeeZone, Heatroom y Reno, los tres en Madrid. Jacobo Suárez asistió las sesiones en el Heatroom y Angel Luján asistió en las sesiones de suma y mástering en Reno. Las fotos son arte de Miguel Pantaleón.

Music, inspiration and life in general is what it is all about for Zoutman. Playing the classical piano in his childhood gave him a head start in his abilities to arrange and compose music. After finishing his Sound Design study at the HKU Art Academy he started working on film sound and music. But still he always spent his spare time on producing techno tracks. This shows that Zoutman is truly passionate about music. Finding balance in contradictions like sound design for movies and producing techno tracks is the main reason why his musical output covers such a wide range of sounds and can be completely different in character. Though these activities seem contradictory, they are not that much apart from each other: Itâ€™s all about the passion for sound and music at the end of the day. As a DJ he has more than 5 years of experience, playing at lots of different places. Zoutmans sound is versatile and strongly depends on the setting and atmosphere of a particular moment. One could say that his sound strongly settles on the crossing borders between Tech House & Techno, but always with shimmering melodies, lurking basslines and a hint of his sound design skills. Late 2010 Zoutman took a new direction and finished his first live set which he has been playing and improving ever since. With a discography of over 30 releases on labels including Dataworx, Globox, Manual Music and LCMTC. Zoutman has established a solid reputation in the producer department ever since his first records came out in 2008. His releases receive massive support from international keyplayers as diverse as Richie Hawtin, Dubfire, Dandi & Ugo, Paco Osuna and Secret Cinema.

Over time this has become more of a Pete Brunelli feed and less of a DOOT feed.  Maybe I will start another SoundCloud, but until then, here is the history... "doot" is a project, a phenomenon, a one-shot-deal that grew some legs.  It started as an offshoot from a band called Doctor Dark, a tribute to Captain Beefheart.  Through that band I met drummer Steve Chillemi, and we spent some time working out parts and playing together, and played a few casual gigs around New Haven, Connecticut.  That led to a collaboration with Eugene Chadbourne on a few live gigs.  Doot has occasionally featured keyboardist Nate Trier!  Doctor Dark played the Zappanale festival in 2006, and Steve and I made a few connections with folks at the Arf Society.  It also led to being invited to perform at the Zappanale festival in 2007 (as a trio with guitarist Andre Cholmondeley), and again in 2009 at the Zappanale Street Party.  Some of the music, the best of it IMO, is minimally structured improvisation over bass loops and noise machines.  Some of it involved performing some pieces based on the compositions of people like Zappa, Hendrix, Beefheart, etc...  As a performing entity, doot no longer exists, but I like keeping this SoundCloud feed around for archival purposes, and as a place to drop some of my electronic composition projects.  If I develop a wrapper for the new stuff, I will spin off a new SoundCloud channel and move the new stuff there.  Feel free to contact me via the SoundCloud profile if you have any questions.

Pete Brunelli

Since 1986 Joseph Nechvatal has worked with ubiquitous electronic visual information, computers and computer-robotics. His computer-robotic assisted paintings and computer software animations are shown regularly in galleries and museums throughout the world. From 1991-1993 he worked as artist-in-resident at the Louis Pasteur Atelier and the Saline Royale / Ledoux Foundation's computer lab in Arbois, France on The Computer Virus Project: an experiment with computer viruses as a creative stratagem. In 2002 he extended that artistic research into the field of viral artificial life through his collaboration with the programmer Stéphane Sikora.

Joseph Nechvatal earned his Ph.D. in the philosophy of art and new technology at The Centre for Advanced Inquiry in the Interactive Arts (CAiiA) University of Wales College, Newport, UK. Dr. Nechvatal presently teaches at the School of Visual Arts in New York City (SVA) and at Stevens Institute of Technology. He writes on art and technology  for “The Thing”, “Intelligent Agent”, “Tema Celeste”, and “Zing”. His book of essays Towards an Immersive Intelligence: Essays on the Work of Art in the Age of Computer Technology is being released by Edgewise Press in early 2009.

Originally hailing from Portugal (Aveiro), DJ/PRODUCER : PHEW (João Miguel Pires), began his career in the art of DJing since the 90”s, heavily influenced by electronic music of the time, starting initially by playing at private parties, like the vast majority of DJs of that time, and in that short time, PHEW acquired a passion for all kinds of electronic music (house, tech-house, techno), that will never die no more.From the private parties, to the main stage of the best clubs and national events & some festivals, DJ PHEW has long been divided between the records, the DJing, and later his other passion: Music Production. His effort and dedication to electronic music resulted in a notable rise in the national club circuit, where he performed alongside top Portuguese artists, through his enormous connection with the public, combined with a refined technique, and one of his strongest points, his taste in music. His sets are characterized by energetic and hi octane style with a multifaceted and eclectic variation of house, tech-house, minimal techno & techno. He has a commitment to diversity by exploring any particular styles of house, tribal & techno. Melodic, progressive and groovy beats are the hallmark of the DJ PHEW style, when combined with his technical skill it creates a steady increase in intensity, pace and energy that infect the audience leading them through a mesmerizing trip and giving no break to people on the dance floor. Track selection is one of his strengths! Deliberately makes use of improvisation, provoking interaction. Sometimes it is accompanied by a groovy beats or by melodic sounds creating atmospheres leading the audience to another dimension. The creativity, enthusiasm and variation lead to every gig being a different party, making each performance unique.During his long career in Portugal marked a permanent presence on the national circuit of the highest level playing in  the most emblematic clubs like: Estação da Luz (Aveiro), Alcatraz (Cantanhede), Pachá (Ofir), Rocks (Porto), I.R.S (Algarve), Horta 2 (Algarve), Via Latina (Coimbra), Ultimatum (Coimbra), Viaáppia (Salgueiro), Republica (Castelo Branco),  Club8Graus(Aveiro),Barbaridades(Algarve), First Club(Cantanhede), Komplexus (Famalicão), etc.., also to playing some times in Spain at the club Joy Eslava (Corunha). But it was only after moving to London to study music production  in (S.A.E -School Audio Engineering), for a couple of years back in 2005 that his passion for making music really began to take hold. During that time he played at the Venues: Sosho Match (Bar/Club, 2 Tabernacle Street, Broadgate, Old Street, London), Bang Bar (Ivory House, St. Katharine Docks, London), and every Sunday Sessions at Lloyds No. 1 (Camden, The Ice Wharf, 28 Jamestown Road, London).In his ceaseless quest for perfection and artistic growth, he felt the need to extend his art to music creation, and finally he assumed the role of producer.His music sits perfectly along the boundries of deep, hypnotic tech house grooves and percussion infused techno beats, appealing to both underground house and techno lovers alike…

Gold Digger are one of London’s most exciting bands, currently on course to explode all over the music world.

The band fuses a conventional band set-up of vocals (Steve Beales, Stephanie Smart), drums (Simon Mooney), Guitar (Anton Howarth) and bass (Richard Snelgrove) together with an electronic mesh of live programming.

Gold Digger recently finished their second album ‘Get It Together’ with Jon Astley (The Who, David Bowie). Most of these tracks were rehearsed and polished at the Premises, East London (Klaxons, Hot Chip, Unkle) over the course of 2007.

The band are now set to deliver a series of exciting series of live performances, with more details of forthcoming festivals soon.

In short, Gold Digger are:

from DJ Bio: "...I was in love with house and DJing when I realised that it wasn't music in the sense of Mozart, but a form of self expression- participating in making a musical collage. Like a musical cut and paste. You get to pick your favourite songs, how fast or slow, or how long you want to play it, which part of the song you want to highlight, whether you want to cut it up or layer it, whether you want the feel to be smooth or charging, whether you want... The combinations are endless w/ house music, and that much fun!"

Just so that you know that we are giving you our best as far as time, energy and love...

We only buy 8-12 vinyl records for every 100 records we listen to.  Jim & I have probably bought over 60crates of house over the years- that's over 6000 records!  We only buy 15-35 tracks for every 1000-2500 mp3's that we listen to. Sometimes less. We are beat junkies and buy every month!!
 
Finally, we only end up playing 80% (or less) of what we buy because it has to give us goosebumps, make us say 'WOW' or make us put our fists in the air when listening to a track and sometimes after you buy, you decide that you don't like the track as much.

 Music is a language used all around the world. Transcending cultural and lingual barriers, this universal code is finding its way even into the most remote corners of the planet. Via the internet, music is connecting people who otherwise would never have got to know each other: Bridging the social context consisting of different cultural backgrounds and languages, music makes us feel united, which is somewhat crazy â€“ music is a CRAZY LANGUAGE. 

Coordinated from Berlin, the netlabel CRAZY LANGUAGE was founded by AXIOM and HURON in 2006. Ever since Crazy Language has been serving as music filter and platform for artistic self-realisation. The label offers all experimental electronic music genres an outlet, for example IDM, Electronica, Glitch, Abstract, Ambient, Downbeat and Breaks. This is reflected in the passion of the netlabel owners as well as in the diversity of the music scene. With lots of love for music, Crazy Language is articulating itself in a dialect spoken all around the world by artists and music lovers alike: the Crazy Language of course.

Very few new imprints have received such a warm welcome from all sides of the spectrum than Room With A View. Respected dj’s, worldwide music media & retailers have all been deeply impressed by the quality & vision transported by the label founded in spring 2009 by Dairmount & Anja Knupper in Hamburg. The label’s ethic is aiming to get back to timeless “emotional content” club music with a futuristic flair, while breaking the pattern of “functionality” that club music too often slips into these days. Room With A View presents a subtle mixture of House & Techno with a twist of freshness & Detroit influences. 

It is quite a little performance to invite a large range of dj’s to enjoy the same sound these days : Techno mammoths such as Carl Craig, Laurent Garnier, Ritchie Hawtin, Dubfire or Dj Hell, Deep House heavyweights such as Jimpster, Dj Deep, Manuel Tur or Brothers Vibe, Tech House masters such as Steve Bug, MANDY or Joris Voorn, Leftfield wizards such as Lawrence, Peter Kruder, Jazzanova or dj legends such as Danny Krivit or Francois K have all embraced the sound of the label with real enthusiasm…

Early in 1994 KREIDLER was founded by Thomas Klein, Andreas Reihse, Detlef Weinrich and Stefan Schneider who was to leave KREIDLER in 1998; his place on bass-guitar was taken by Alexander Paulick (of Coloma and Narrow Bridges).

Kreidler's album Riva was released 1994 on a small Parisian label. This was to be the first of 23 releases to date, with the latest ABC in 2014.

Among the artists to have been remixed by KREIDLER are Einstürzende Neubauten, Depeche Mode, Faust, or Eurythmics. Their musical collaborations include Klaus Dinger (NEU!, la Düsseldorf), Add (N) to X, Pyrolator, Young Gods, Momus, Leo Garcia, Theo Altenberg, or Chicks on Speed.

KREIDLER have played over 300 shows throughout Europe, Asia and America. In techno clubs, in rock venues, in concert halls. At festivals like Sonar, Roskilde or Cervantino. In museums and art galleries: at the Van Dyck retrospective in Antwerp, for Rosemarie Trockel, Mike Kelley or in New York's Museum of Modern Art and in the Centre Pompidou Paris for the openings of Andreas Gursky.

KREIDLER contributed to artists books such as Deutsch -Young German Photography, Toit du Monde, Romantik. Their videos are screened at festivals e.g. in Barcelona, Valencia, Baden-Baden, and Munich. Au-Pair, La Casa, and Moth Race were awarded at Internationale Kurzfilmtage Oberhausen.

KREIDLER music is used in films, plays and in the modern-dance - e.g. in Pina Bausch's Ten Chi, it has graced the catwalks of Chanel, Lacoste, or Giles Deacon.

KREIDLER composed the soundtracks for Alexandra Sell's acclaimed movie Durchfahrtsland / Remote Area / Terre de Transit, for Tommy Pallotta's / Femke Wolting's The Last Hijack, and for Heinz Emigholz' The Airstrip. Emigholz accompanied KREIDLER's album DEN in 2012/13 with 7 films; his forthcoming movie 2+2=22 (The Alphabet) centers around KREIDLER's recording session in Tbilisi for their 2014 album ABC (on Bureau b), which is accompanied by film in 6 chapters by Lior Shamriz.

The mixed-genre set may seem like a daunting prospect to many DJs and Producers, but for Sébastien Christophe Becky it means a set without limitations, enabling him to take chances on the endlessly enthralling journey of sound which has catapulted him to success in the infancy of his DJing and Producing career. 
      
      Sébastien grew up in Cologne Germany; son of accomplished rock and roll drummer music has always been his passion. He began his journey at age 14 playing bass in a punk rock band. His potential later overlapped into the more technical side of music as he interned at various professional music studios through out Cologne as a studio engineer. Sébastien Becky wasted no time in asserting himself in the music business with his first record deal at age 18 with Hamburg based Superstition records. Climbing up the music ladder and strengthening his talent with his move to Berlin in 1996 becoming part of the vital electronic scene with successful gigs at Tresor, Panasonic and numerous other underground clubs. 
      
      He as secured countless records released throughout the 90’s under prominent labels like Analog Records USA, Formic Records, Essence Records and Polimorph Records, to name a few, using various aliases such as Adilette Man, KDS, DJ KDS, DJ Cream, Puke Slaughter, Criz Heaven and Police in Cars.  In accordance to his many successful and vital record contributions he has created several of his own labels (Fixed System Records, Salz, and UADR)
      
      His versatile and unique sound is well known as he has years of experience touring as an international DJ at some of the best clubs in the most exciting cities throughout Berlin, Cologne, London, Ibiza, and more recently NYC.
      
      After a musical pause Sébastien Becky is back as adilette-man and dj_kds with a new start, again showcasing his flexibility and fresh unique sound with a more diverse musical direction. Reinventing his art and expanding his musical talent, experimenting with trance and other genres. Creating remixes for other respected and well known DJ’s like Scott Bond & Solarstone under the name 2human DJ’s as well as international DJ Abel Riballo. He is also featured as the producing genius for Shoutbox Records, stretching his creative style in writing tracks and collaborating with Abel Riballo on diverse directions of electronic music.
      
      Sébastien is an artist who is constantly looking to push the envelope in his music carrier. With many releases to come in 2009 he has proved that his fresh, modern, and smooth sound that is filled with his organic passion for music is something that is much anticipated by electronic, techno, and minimal techno lovers everywhere.

If persistence and passion is a recipe for success, Nate Laurence (Minneapolis, MN, USA) characterizes the journey. Nate is, of course, the quadruple threat: veteran DJ since 1994, prolific producer, event-coordinator, and label owner.

Nate has always been a DJ first. Once known as DJ Unity – a patron of former Minneapolis RAVE troupe “UNIK Communications” – Nate has labored for his place in house music. A career that developed over the course of a decade – largely behind the scenes – has now become impossible to ignore. Amid absurd energy behind the decks – layered with dexterous turntablism – Nate impresses even the most cynical critics one at a time “leaving wows in his wake.” Today, Nate remains active with gigs reaching as far as Europe, Southern Africa, and throughout the United States. Though national and international bookings keep him busy, in 2009 Nate fulfilled an enduring aspiration and true privilege by becoming a resident DJ at the legendary First Avenue Nightclub in Minneapolis.

After living in his second home of Cape Town, South Africa in 2001, Nate focused on production. Since then, his discog has grown at a reputable pace. With rookie releases on Flatpack Traxx, Funkfield, and Control Recordings, Nate proved his aptitude as a gifted producer. His distinct production style has continued to mature, signing EPs with Spatula City, Guesthouse, Love Network, Onethirty, Mindtravel, and Flapjack Records to name but a few. In 2007, Nate partnered with Chicago-based beatmaker, Scrubfish (Scott Kammer) and together they continue to reach Top100 lists worldwide while each new release continues to outshine subsequent releases.

In 2008 Nate created “HotDish.” HotDish is both a collaborative of DJs (Nate and good friend J Matthews) and an event crew that has become an illustrious house movement in Minneapolis. Finally, in 2011 Nate began a new philanthropic record label, Pluralistic Records. Pluralistic Records releases distinct and unique tracks that cross the boundaries between Chicago, Detroit, disco house, and tech house...or simply, house. 

Notably, Nate (the academic) is also a Social Justice advocate, activist, and educator working at the University of Minnesota. This part of him is infused in his music, his branding, and all that he works to accomplish. Keep your eyes open for this talented and very different househead - who continues to give his all to keep the music fresh and far-reaching.

Always having nourished a deep passion for music, Tiago D'Herbe was influenced by the different kinds of music he heard from his young parents but also by performing at incidental music encounters in cafés and friendly gigs. His discovery of alternative, electronic and progressive music was inevitable.

In 2001, he built his first home studio, used to explore music composition and mixtures initially with a simple software-based set-up. He also developed DSP modules that he later used in his music.

His background in computer engineering and development of specific methods of music composition gave him the necessary confidence to start composing D'Herbe Foundation's debut album Inner|Face, which was released in 2006.

In 2007, D'Herbe Foundation was invited to score the original soundtrack for the play "Eu Ligo-te". This was an unique opportunity to create less digital music. 

The music of D'Herbe Foundation is hybrid and unique, fusing the genres of techno, dub, chill-house, experimental, classical, World music and jazz. He is particularly proud to have collaborated with talented musicians including Maria João, Shout!, producer José da Ponte and some very good friends.

Originally getting exposed to the rave scene in Fredericton's (New Brunswick, Canada) warehouse parties in the early '90s, Psylozen got serious about djing once he moved to Halifax (Nova Scotia, Canada) in the spring of '99.  The decade since then has led him deep into the fractal forests of psychedelic sounds, leaving him with a unique taste in music.  Favouring long, multilayered mixes, today he is one of only a handful of people on the east coast of Canada championing the psychedelic music that traces it's lineage directly to the Hippy movement of the '60s.  When he's not busy playing at Psy festivals and events in Quebec and Ontario, he is promoting special one-off events as part of the Nova Psychotia collective.

Psylozen will take you through a universe of music from all around the world, fusing old with new, digital with analog, leaving no turn unstoned.

Always having nourished a deep passion for music, Tiago D'Herbe was influenced by the different kinds of music he heard from his young parents but also by performing at incidental music encounters in cafés and friendly gigs. His discovery of alternative, electronic and progressive music was inevitable.

In 2001, he built his first home studio, used to explore music composition and mixtures initially with a simple software-based set-up. He also developed DSP modules that he later used in his music.

His background in computer engineering and development of specific methods of music composition gave him the necessary confidence to start composing D'Herbe Foundation's debut album Inner|Face, which was released in 2006.

In 2007, D'Herbe Foundation was invited to score the original soundtrack for the play "Eu Ligo-te". This was an unique opportunity to create less digital music. 

The music of D'Herbe Foundation is hybrid and unique, fusing the genres of techno, dub, chill-house, experimental, classical, World music and jazz. He is particularly proud to have collaborated with talented musicians including Maria João, Shout!, producer José da Ponte and some very good friends.

Kid Fury (born Franklin Noel Humphrey) is an MC and DJ hailing from Oxford, UK (not to be confused with the US blogger of the same name)

Kid Fury likens himself to a boxing journeyman in being someone that has for close to two decades exhibited all the right components to be one of the best at his chosen craft, but due to the rigors and joys of real life has rarely been afforded the time to focus completely on his dream.

Unafraid of being pigeon-holed as “old school” for wanting to adhere to the culture and values that originally made hip hop great, his musical tastes are spread far and wide but it is the feeling of having to mix, cut, scratch or juggle something in a particular way for it to be hip hop or when rapping knowing where the line in the sand is between hip hop and pop is that separate him from so many involved in the business of hip hop these days.

It would seem that Kid Fury has become a sort of “jack of all trades” type character known for being a rapper, DJ, radio personality, lover, father, promoter and music industry desk jockey and pen pusher, but would dispute and do what it takes to dispute the premise that he is yet to master any of the above.

Equally as adept on the mic as on the turntables he started building a rep for himself on 'Da Boom Box' radio show which was recognised as one of the country’s top shows in Hip Hop Connection in 2000 before going on to feature on DJ Harry Love’s first single ‘Ill Lyrical Behaviour’ before going through a period in life he only eludes to by saying “I should make more of a point of goin’ on about being one of those dudes that hip hop saved”

Finally back in the lab with an amazing group of beat makers and artists working on what would be a first solo release since appearing on ‘Ill Lyrical Behaviour’ after years of only flirting with the idea of making something to give back for “the free pass” his early achievements have given him.

Having opened live shows on the turntables and as a host for long time co-conspirator Chima Anya, Grandmaster Flash, Pharoahe Monch, Jean Grae, Jay Electronica, GZA, DOOM, Slum Village, Homeboy Sandman, Stalley, Wale, Speech Debelle, Rodney P and can add many more names to this list when we look at who he has conversed with in radio interviews who he has worked with in his various PR roles.

An artist who revels in the idea that his journey thus far has been less about the fame and fortune and more an elevation towards the legacy he'd like to leave behind. Having dipped in and out of the public eye sporadically Kid Fury has around 20 of personal achievements of which he admits to being either very proud of or humbled by... with all that said he really is only just getting started.

Auradrone is a creative force of passion and innovation, fast-forwarding us into a new sonic epoch. Masterminded by the multi-talented Jon Mack, Auradrone mixes sensuality and deep spirit into ultramodern post-rock electronic music, creating a multimedia experience with maximized appeal: to heal and transform, to bring you back to yourself, and then take you elsewhere.

Jon began faceting her diamond at an early age, singing, teaching herself guitar, and forming the mystical vision that propels her today. A child of the theater, she become active in chorus and drama in high school, continuing studies at the Tisch School of Arts at NYU and the Lee Strasberg Institute in Los Angeles. Taking all conventional learning and expanding it to a higher level, she has transcended her craft beyond the simple artistic action and has used the heat from every fire to forge newer elements with which to experiment...and to transform into alchemist's gold.

While performing at major Los Angeles rock clubs and developing the material for Auradrone's debut release, 'Whitelite Britelite', Jon's music and stage persona caught the interest of industry heavyweights who have aided her in developing Auradrone's signature sound. Absorbing these inspirations, she records, mixes, remixes and produces her own material in addition to performance and writing. The result is a diverse and innovative sound that entertains the mind and body alike, resonating to the frequencies of your modern life.

"Whitelite Britelite" is scheduled for release on March 2, 2009, ending the first decade of a new millennium with a sound ahead of the curve in progressive American music. Are you ready? We are already there....

Le Boucher is a dj who mixed between 1996 and 2000, some Tech and Darkcore Drum & Bass in Quebec City for CKRL. At first, it was to be formed to replace Dan Rochette at his radio show "Arts Sonics" when he needed that (4-5 times), with his best friend Kressel. But that become very fun to play all together (Dan, Kressel and LeBoucher every friday nights) and they did that as often as possible during 2 years. After he finished his Master in UI Design in Québec City (beside Kressel), he quickly moved in Montreal and start doing Techno live sets in solo but also in duo with Kressel. He mixed mostly as a Minimal Techno dj after 2004. In 2006, he founded the Eresys artist collective, with friends (Monopoly, Kressel, Dauc, Kasteniede, Yan Leigh, Joystick, FuAncko and Sequential Factory). He stop doing live sets after the launch to concentrate on management, websites design, coding. He also rent 2 music studios, with some partners, to produced events, tracks and podcasts. He left the Montréal scene in 2016 after celebrating Eresys 10 years of activities, on the big scene, at the Montreal Piknic Electronique. Since then, he just mix for fun to concentrate on his job of UI Senior Designer at Bandsintown, to help other musician in the world, with their promotion tools. Since november 2019, he mix officially once a month for a radio station called "La Face B". His radio show is called "No Future" (dystopian electronic music of all kind, really dark, really heavy). The genres he play now are mainly: Dark Ambient, Smooth & Dark Dubstep / Grime, Industrial, Halftime D&B, Neurostep and of course, a bit of Dark Minimal Techno he still love so much.

The Berlin based Gebrüder Teichmann are the two brothers Andi and Hannes Teichmann who work as musicians, DJs and producers and cultural activists. Their work is not limited by style or genre borders. With their musical and cultural projects the two try to find new ways to build bridges.

With their special live electronic setup they collaborate with artists from a wide range of genres, from hip hop to classical music, from traditional to experimental music.

In the field of contemporary music they´ve worked with ensembles as Ensemble Modern or Ensemble Decoder and composers as Moritz Eggert or Leopold Hurt.
Beside that they perform with their father Uli Teichmann as Teichmann & Söhne.
The improvisation trio not only brings together two generations of german avantgarde musicians, but combines elements of world, freejazz, ambient, techno and krautrock.
As networkers they brothers developed intercultural projects in cooperation with Goethe Institutes around the world.

Since 2009 they have put together the project BLNRB with the Goethe-Institut Kenya including artists like Modeselektor, Jahcoozi, Just a Band, Ukoo Flani beside others and are part of the TEN CITIES project management, a research and collaboration project, focusing on history and present of the underground club scenes in the European cities of Berlin, Bristol, Kyiv, Lisbon and Naples and the African cities of Johannesburg, Cairo, Luanda, Lagos and Nairobi. Soundcamp Sri Lanka, the Mondmaschine Project in Mexico and Soundcamp Karachi follwoed. 
They curated several nights at Worldtronic Festival at Haus der Kulturen der Welt, Berlin.

Their diverse musical activities DJing, giving workshops and playing live have taken them to over 60 countries as far as Afghanistan, Angola or Honduras.

Gebrüder Teichmann started getting into music in 1989 at the age of 9 and 12 years with their punk band Totalschaden before they discovered electronic music.
They´ve been an active part of the Berlin underground scene since the late 90s and have been playing all relevant Berlin clubs from Berghain/Panorama Bar, WMF to Bar25.
Since 2009 they are hosting regular nights at Suicide Circus Berlin.
Together and solo they have released on various labels, such as Kompakt, Ladomat, Killekill, Staubgold, Soundway, Outhere or Disko B and their own labels Festplatten, Teichtracks, NOLAND and NOLAND Tracks.

Noxxer is a portuguese DJ and producer.

He started mixing and playing, back in 2004, in his hometown Almeirim (Portugal). Noxxer moved to Coimbra in 2005 and his gigs quickly brought him to perform all around Portugal, playing in several clubs, bars and outdoor parties in Coimbra, Figueira da Foz, Águeda, Santarém or all over the Alentejo region. 2009 saw his international debut, playing in german clubs Ruefetto, Kamikaze and Parabel (Freiburg im Breisgau). He is currently not playing many venues, although you can find him performing occasionally in his hometown.

By the end of 2007, he has released his first remix through the american label Decibel NYC ("Spies"), starting then a long collaboration with the label that led him to remix 6 tracks until 2009. The first original EP came in 2008 ("Minimal Solutions 4 Maximum Problems") and was followed by the "Pleasure" EP in 2010. 2009 also saw his debut in Arteria Music Label, an italian music group, where he released a remix and a single ("Queima"). He already remixed artists like Mad Cows, the Undah-Dub, Vladimir Neuymin, J-Deep, Mauro Del Principe, Adam Clay or Grier, having also unofficially reworked lots of tracks. His latest release was a collaboration with his friend Undah-Dub called "Lucky Biatch".

He is currently on a hiatus for undetermined time.

LALA has had various experiences with several music genres becoming very versatile with her art. Early on she joined a Chinese singing talent contest held by the major Canadian Chinese station, Fairchild TV, singing in both Mandarin and Cantonese. Being westernized, LALA did not speak Cantonese or Mandarin at the time, but worked very hard to learn the songs, winning second place. The contest had national radio, television, and print media coverage, and LALA was immediately recognized, becoming popular in the Chinese community across Canada. She continued to develop her relationship with Fairchild Television and shortly thereafter entered the David Foster’s Make-A-Wish Foundation talent search. LALA was one of the 10 finalists in the Vancouver region. It was there she sang for the likes of David Foster, Sue Foster, Clay Aiken, and Babyface.

It October 2006, LALA completed her Masters degree in Education. Afterward she left her music elementary teaching position and other gigs so she could move to New York to pursue her music career. Since then she has made several connections working with major production teams and has started showcasing her own music. She’s appeared on radio, in music videos, collaborated with other artists, musicians, DJs, choreographers, and dancers. In February 2007, LALA came in second place at The Verizon Sing contest in the Chinese New Year Chinatown Parade in New York. She also performed for the parade in February 2010. She has revisited her involvement (as a solo artist) with Claviscape, LLC in Connecticut where her single, “Shooting Stars” was released.

In August 2007, LALA opened up for award winning singer/songwriter, Michael McDonald, Davy Jones from The Monkees, Michael Bolton, Dru Hill, and Aretha Franklin. She also won 1st place in an industry showcase competition put on by SRC Universal Records.

LALA kicked off the 2009 New Year by performing the National Anthem at NJ Nets first game of the year at IZOD Centre which was broadcasted on Fox Sports, Yeshd, and Bloomberg Radio. Her music is played on various Satellite radio, college radio, online radio, mixtapes, and clubs throughout the U.S., Asia, and Europe. Her R&B single, “This Is Why I Fell” received responses from over 400 DJs and radio hosts via Digiwaxx Media LLC. In March and April of 2009, LALA’s songs were in rotation on iTunes Radio Jamz Hits 1FM.

Vibrant with the diverse scenes and audiences in New York, LALA performed at various Gay clubs including LGBT venues, events, and Pride festivals throughout the States. She then turned more toward Dance music and began working with various dance producers and DJs. Her single “I Will Never Forget You” landed on BPM and OUTQ Sirius XM radio, Party 105.3 FM and other stations within the U.S. and Europe. During this buzz, LALA and ManiaCalm productions were offered various label deals. In December 2009, the single signed with Red Stick/Strictly Rhythm Records. This impressive debut, finished at number 7 on BPM’s top 50 of 2010 (Sirius Radio), number 8 on AOL’s top 10 Dance songs of 2010 and peaked at #5 on Hot Dance Radio Airplay for Billboard Magazine in July 2010.

In January, 2011, LALA continued to work with ManiaCalm and co-wrote a second single, “I Miss You”. Recently, Next Plateau Entertainment (home of Salt N’ Pepper and Nina Sky) signed the single and plans to promote the record further. The single is playing on BPM XM Sirius and various other Dance radio stations. Reviews and article features on LALA have been in various LGBT newspapers, magazines, and online radio stations throughout the States, such as Out at Night Magazine, Florida Agenda Newspaper, Out and About live radio, to name a few.

LALA is currently signed to Big Management and is working on her next single release. She is driven to become a success story. When asked by an interviewer what fuels her to be so unstoppable and driven, LALA answered, “God has given me a talent, and I am going to take it to the fullest!”

Keep an eye out for her upcoming shows in the NYC area.

DJ SHADEE was rocking every club in the New York/Metropolitan area, a Colombian born kid but raised in Astoria, Queens. At age 16, DJ SHADEE was introduced to the turntables and soon after fell in love with the idea of mastering this craft. In 1999 DJ SHADEE debuted on the "club scene" with his initial performance at Club Twirl. Soon after, SHADEE broke into the club scene playing at the likes of NuBar Lounge, Supper Club,& China Club and Jade Terrace on a regular basis. By 2001, SHADEE'S star was burning bright establishing himself as a dominant party rocker in several upscale venues per week. Since then, SHADEE has performed at numerous venues in the tri-state area building an impressive resume which includes BED, CROBAR, RETOX, MSG, GUESTHOUSE, SPIRIT, BLVD, MARQUE, HOME, LOTUS, SUPPER CLUB, MYST, PROVIDENCE, TRIBECCA NIGHT CLUB, CLUB MANSION (MIAMI), OPIUM GARDEN (MIAMI), ELEMENTS (P.R.)and the world famous COPACABANA just to name a few. This notoriety to the masses made SHADEE a household name in NYC's competitive club scene.
  
  In the meantime, while continuing to work hard in the clubs, he caught the attention of another DJ by the name of ALEX SENSATION. Alex was already well recognized and respected in the Latin community as the lead DJ on New York's #1 station, LA MEGA 97.9. Along with his daily show La Mega Mezcla del Mediodia, SHADEE worked with Alex Sensation in several different venues where the dynamic duos mixing and record selection continued to move the party. Working with Alex was a milestone for DJ SHADEE, providing him with the forum to spin on live broadcasts from the legendary Copacabana to thousands of listeners throughout the tri-state area. That relationship formed a bond between Alex Sensation and SHADEE that prompted him to inquire about a hand picked DJ crew called, The DJ KINGS, of which Alex Sensation was an integral member. Upon recommendation from Alex, there was no doubt THE DJ KINGS wanted SHADEE to be an intricate part of this elite group of DJ's.
  
  So what's next for DJ SHADEE on a professional level, you ask? Recently he has expanded his travel schedule to include destinations like Puerto Rico, Miami, and even Hawaii just to name a few. In addition, he can also be spotted at a growing list of celebrity car shows including DUB magazine, Hot Import Nights, and the Funk Master Flex celebrity car show. He's also become more involved with his original love interest from a music perspective, mixing and distributing numerous mix cd's throughout the tri-state area. Currently, SHADEE continues to play at 3 to 4 clubs a week aside from his own venue, NuBar Lounge in Queens New York. Wether SHADEE's rocking a trendy club in New York City or the beautiful islands of Purto Rico and Hawaii, there's no crowd he can't handle.

Pentagonik was founded in Berlin in 2005 as a platform for electronic music and events. Pentagonik consists of two branches dedicated to releasing high-quality electronic music.

Following many successful releases on the Pentagonik netlabel - available online at www.pentagonik.de under creative commons licensing - the group founded the new Pentagonik Digital Label in 2008, bringing the label's music to the major digital distribution platforms. Pentagonik's artists span a broad range of styles and influences, from minimal to techhouse and beyond.

Regular events have included the Pentagonik series at Watergate (Berlin) and collaborations with various event agencies throughout Berlin. Currently, the Pentagonik series is enjoying a successful run at the Arena Club in Berlin.

Throcke is the creation of Christopher Mollineaux Carson. It is a solo studio project involving electronic and organic elements - distorted organs, cascading drums and soothing guitar melodies as well as quirky clicks and blurps. Occasionally there are layers of vocals, or perhaps a windy wash of rain. Throcke works such disparate textures into complex, melodic grooves to craft a truly original sound. The results are both accessible and constantly surprising.
Throcke self-produced his debut EP Advance Longing in 2005, followed by a string of single tracks. He then slowed down the songwriting for a few years while playing drums for the band UMAMI. 2009 marks his return, with the full-length album Sometimes Not Unpointful.

The project Mathon has its name from a beautiful place in the Swiss Alps. Every year since 2003 Thomas Augustiny, Roger Stucki and Pete Leuenberg meet there and invite different musicians, to translate the impressive surrounding into music. The conceptual project is ambient music by its original definition: space becomes sound and sound generates space. This way four albums have been recorded, together with Ronny Spiegel, Maria Capelli, Nocolas Kellner and Maurice de Martin. The growing interest for the visualisation of the music, lead to installation for Etoy, HKB or the museum for communication. The pieces of the current release were remixed by international known musicians like; Kenneth Kirschner, i8u, SteinbrÃ¼chel or Digitalis.

from improvisation to freedom in structures - shannon nyquist is a dresden and leipzig based ambient-postrock band consisting of denis nareike (git,dr,bg,synth), rené tekker jugoldt (synths) and antje meichsner (synth). 

we are experimenting with our instruments and with techniques from other improvisational genres like singing, performance and experimental radio shows including the post-production and our communication about the creative process. occasionally we question our habitual play. we are inspiring ourselves by slide shows or special scents and perfumes.

we are researching methods to make our music repeatable on stage. that means we are experimenting in an area of conflict: we'd like to achieve as much freedom as possible on one hand and sufficient footing by scores on the other hand to express the moment concentrated and intuitively. 


band history: 
in summer 2007 the anti-rockist-section of the former psychedelic-postrock band face-about-face met in the rehearsel room again: denis nareike (git), dorit horn (bg), rené jugold (synth, git). antje meichsner (synth) joined them. denis advanced himself in playing the drums and bought an old korg ms10. they found a new and more inward way to make music: getting away from song structures by improvising and experimenting. their playing turned to ambient and postrock. in the following autumn and winter many breakouts of creativitiy happened. many hours of intense and inspiring material were recorded. in the additional soundcloud player there are some favorites from that period.
spring 2008 was a difficult time for them. in summer dorit quit the band. denis and antje are playing the bass now.

[Michigander / FXHE / Planet-E ]
As the world watches the renaissance and revival of Detroit, it listens for the sound of those carrying the torch of authentic Motor City-born techno into the future. Brian Kage is one of those innovators leading Detroit’s electronic music forward into the musical zeitgeist of change and revolution. 

Kage was recently crowned one of DJ magazine’s “10 Detroit Producers Keeping the Sound of the Motor City Alive.”

Detroit born-and-raised Kage co-founded record label Beretta Music, through which he mentored and helped shape the careers of many internationally respected DJs and producers.  Kage has also released well-received music on Omar S’s record label FXHE, Carl Craig’s Planet-E, Steve Bug’s PokerFlat, Rob Modell’s Echospace, and many more. Kage’s “DetroitLuv” record was featured and played on BBC Radio 1’s Essential Mix by Richie Hawtin and Ricardo Villalobos.

Kage’s “The Arc EP,” released on his own Michigander label, pays tribute to Detroit with its uplifting melodic techno style. “The Arc EP” was also featured and praised on Resident Advisor’s “New Tracks” list. Additionally, DJ magazine praised his collaboration with vocalist James Garcia, ‘Shut Your Eyes’, as “one of 2015’s best house tracks.” 

When he’s not working on his own music, Brian is working alongside local and international acts to mix, master and engineer their music with “KageMastering.” 

A vital part of Detroit’s rich techno history, Brian Kage is one of the artists and producers providing the score for the Motor City’s continuing rebirth. This is the sound of the future. This is Brian Kage.

Sheep Vs. Robots offers digital audio production services for music, television, film, and commercials.

Artist roster includes: Karoshi, Cibachrome, The Piano Movers, The Droolies, BMW Cockfight, Right Turn Clyde, Apollo Cake, Golden Sun Revolver

We wanna go somewhere else. We're not threatened by people anymore. All our insecurities have evaporated. We're in the clouds now. We're wide open. We're spacemen orbiting the earth. The world looks beautiful from here, man. We're nympholeptics, desiring for the unobtainable. We risk sanity for moments of temporary enlightenment. So many ideas. So little memory. The last thought killed by anticipation of the next. We embrace an overwhelming feeling of love. We flow in unison. We're together. I wish this was real. We want a universal level of togetherness, where we're comfortable with everyone. We're in rhythm. Part of a movement. A movement to escape. We wave goodbye. Ultimately, we just want to be happy. Heh, yeah, hang on, what the fuck was I just talking about?

- Human Traffic, 1999

Bio:
A serious career in producing electronic music almost always starts in a club: everyone knows the story of his first night out at some legendary place, sometimes behind the turntables, more often than not in front of them. Everybody remembers how this sound hit him for the first time, how the doors to the paradise of the steady bassdrum opened. The hero of our story found its initiation at Aufschwung Ost, famous predecessor to the fabulous Stammheim Kassel, which may be defunct but still resides as referential limbo in the hearts of many. However, music hasn't been a stranger for the then 16 years old Martin: already the first portable radio was manipulated for the first steps towards sampling, the belt-driven turntables were scratched to death and the amiga 500 gobbed primal hip hop beats. Although nothing of this sounded like Public Enemy or A Tribe Called Quest it still sufficed to make the young apprentice's mouth water. Then Techno came along with its massive impact, followed by the first shaky dj gig in front of a real crowd at Aufschwung Ost, the first Akai sampler, the first Atari computer, the first field recording, the first loops on 123 BPM, finally the movement to Cologne, being a techno stronghold back then. It's a near classic biography for Martin Beume who has grown to become one respected producer and DJ, but without the attitude. He prefers to stay in the background and lets the music take the center stage. But he who inhales the groove has to exhale at some point too, so Martin's first demo tracks landed at Sub Static, where he released two EP's under his monicker Golden Red. Both featured chopped up funk with a warm-hearted flavour and rank amongst the classics of the label. With Pawas, Martin found a kindred spirit to produce some great tracks for Adam Kroll's Squonk outlet or the people at Brut. That's also the point where Martin found the guts to embark on a solo career under his civic name, which has been a wise decision as the first 12â€œ on Outils Du Connaisseur arrestingly shows.
