Dj from Manchester UK playing Trance and Tech Trance using nothing more that a Pacemaker Dj Tool.

He adores the Pacemaker.net tool and does all his mixes with it while on his travels. The mixes take inspiration from the things around him and the mix style is different from what you usually hear. More in your face and more frantic that most mixes, it leads you on a journey somewhere else.  

He use to dj under the name of Adrenalin Rush in and around the South west of England and Wales on Vinyl believe it or not but gave it up when he moved to London. Djing on laptops was the name of the game then and he gained a regular spot on a Miami based internet radio station before it got shut down in 2005.

Maniatika is the fusion of artists Raimon Jc and Rockoder.



Raimon began his musical career in 1993 attending to music, guitar, and bass guitar lessons at the Conservatori de Girona, and also a Jazz and modern music school. After several years in different bands where he got various concerts around Spain, he evolved until beginning in the world of electronic music. As a DJ, he has been part of associations like Oval-Music or Sanae Group, playing sets in many clubs along the likes of Le Rachdingue, Eixclub, La Sala del Cel, KGB, etc.

After settling in this music style, and evolving as a DJ, in 2004 he began his career as a producer. From this stage the most outstanding tracks like “Expression”, “Rotation”, “Insomni, or digital productions like “Alone”, “Discharge Combustion”, edited by himself under his own label, Hypnotic Creations.



Rockoder began his musical career back in 1999. He started of DJing until he progressed until he found his own musical style. After a few years playing in different clubs, he entered in Sanae Group, its only then when he really settles as a DJ, playing in venues like La Sala del Cel, Le Rachdingue, Palm Beach Club, Oxid…

In 2003, the Senglar Rock festival included electronic music in their line-up for the first time ever, where Rockoder stunned all the attendants with one of his best sets ever.

After Sanae Group slowly fell apart, he became part of Hypnotic Creations, beginning here his career as a producer. His vast knowledge about computers have helped him evolve quickly in this new environment and quickly master the different devices that he has acquired over the years. 



From the joining of their experiences, they both began at a new level, where they put behind all that had been achieved to the date, to start working on live electronic sets, thus the beginning of their project Maniatika.

In their sets you can see a strong connexion between them and a carefully worked style, having up to seven tracks playing simultaneously. Its obvious by now that just playing on decks has become too small for them now, and they are thinking bigger by playing a live format, this way being able to play infinite amounts of sounds, effects and tracks making even the lazying clubber dance.


Their preferences are playing live, or live-jockey, but they know very well that they aren’t going to stop producing.

Juan Pablo Maturana, a.k.a Aphonic was born in 1988 in Mexico. He discovered music through his father. Jean Michel-Jarre, Pink Floyd were childhood favorites. As a teen he used to play drums on a Psychedelic Rock Band experimenting with sounds, it was not until his late teenage years he discovered electronic music, to wich he was immediately attracted to and was completely blown away by the energy and the originality of the sounds being used. It was so new and fresh to him as a musician that he needed to figure out how this music was made, so he quit the band and began collecting drum machines and synths. After having finished high school he decided to study music production at Londonâ€™s Point Blank Music School. He lived one year in London, being influenced by the scene and great clubs such as Fabric, he truly experienced electronic music. Maturana uses his productions to explore percussive elements, dubby basslines. Maturana aims to transmit instantaneous human emotions through electronic sounds. He is currently planning to expand his musical creativity to Field Recording.

Bytz (aka Medium) has been producing all flavors of electronic music and audio experimentation for nearly two decades. Since 2011, he has been instrumental in the rise of Brooklyn as a center of electronic music, curating and producing over a thousand events in New York City, encompassing techno, house, bass music, dub, sound art, and jazz.

Bytz has performed on 4 continents, including in Berlin, Paris, Bangkok, Kyiv, Bombay, Guatemala, Lisbon, and Hanoi; at the Mysteryland, Elements, and Gather festivals; at acclaimed warehouse parties such as Blkmarket Membership and Rinsed; at top nightclubs in NYC, including Output, Cielo, Elsewhere, and Sullivan Room; and has held residencies at TBA Brooklyn, National Underground and Bossa Nova Civic Club. He founded Secret Guests collective in 2014, and co-founded the critically acclaimed Bushwick A/V afterhours series.

More recently, he has turned his attention to Asia, producing the RE:FIX Festival in Bangkok and co-founding the deepcover parties on Koh Phangan island, in addition to working as a partner in Underground Music Thailand - UMT.radio, to showcase artists from all over Thailand. During an era without live events, he has continued to contribute, appearing on livestreams for Charivari Detroit, Burning Man Worldwide, and Grey Area.

Started Dj-ing in 80s at indie gigs and then on pirate radio/tv station Network 21. Opened his first club in 1985, Toured as DJ with The Shamen, then signed with Rising High Records for the albums Flying High, Global Chillage. Joined up with Pete Namlook to record two albums as Dreamfish. Did two sessions for BBC's John Peel. Residencies at underground clubs like Lost and Megatripolis. Remixed Coldcut's Autumn Leaves which went on to become a classic. Played at Love Parade and Glastonbury festival throughout the 90s. 

Wrote for NME, Mixmag and i-D magazine, presented The Chill Out Zone on Kiss FM.Toured Europe, USA and Japan repeatedly, made mix CDs like The Morning After, Abstract Funk Theory, God Bless The Chilled. Signed with Ninja Tunes and made the album Its Tomorrow Already and singles Nepalese Bliss & Fish Dances. Got involved with the Big Chill at the very beginning in 1994 and played every year since for them. Appeared in the cult movie Modulations. Recorded an album in Japan with Jonah Sharp and Harry Hosono of YMO. Made a TV commercial, soundtracked a play on Radio 3 and remixed the Dr Who theme for the BBC. Talked about Brian Eno on C4. Moved his Nubient club to Big Chill Bar. Won Ibiza Chillout DJ of the year - twice. Did two mixes for Rob da Banks show on Radio 1. Remixed Anne Garner and 6th Sense. Made an Altermodern podcast for the Tate Britain.  2010 won Best Downtempo DJ again, and started new job running Apollo label as part of R+S...

This beautiful song tells the story of Schapelle Corby, an innocent suffering extreme cruelty in the hell of an Indonesian prison cell. 

Schapelle was subjected to the most harrowing of show trials, in which evidence and justice were simply diversions to be dismissed as quickly as possible. She was sentenced to a barbaric 20 years for importation of marijuana, a crime which she could not have committed. She is still there now: suffering. 

Tara Hack recorded this outstanding song at the end 2008, in New York. It is a remarkable track, from a hugely talented emerging artist. A beautiful song and a beautiful voice for a desperate cause. 

Hopefully it will help spread awareness of Schapelle's plight to a wider audience. Please remember that Schapelle's cries for justice are ignored, her tears are not seen, and her voice is not heard: but YOU can become her voice. Please pass on her story, this song, and our Schapelle videos to friends, to colleagues, to anyone who will listen.

Please Don't Walk Away... visit schapelle.net

Earthling is the solo project of DJ Celli. Psychedelic blast-off music to lose your marbles to. Celli's other projects include: Everblast, Soundaholix, Vatos Locos, and Third Ear Audio

Ibiza based Celli has been partying and producing in the Psychedelic trance scene since its beginnings in the early 90's.

From his roots as an underground party organiser in Ibiza he soon started producing music releasing his first track "Just Say Yes" on T.I.P. Records in 1999, followed by his debut album entitled "Patterns" on Acidance Records in 2001

He has since produced a further two albums he has now released an astounding 250 tracks, and 12 albums under various pseudonyms such as : Soundaholix (with GMS) , Third Ear Audio ( with Nick Doof), Vatos Locos and Everblast (with Chromatone), Celli rocks dancefloors, bringing his unique psychedelic sound to the far reaches of the planet... His Earthling LIVE shows showcase his best music and always unreleased cutting edge tracks as well

He is also an exceptional DJ - doing extended DJ sets at many of the big Psychedelic festivals 

He is part of the Zero1 Music record label. Zero 1 Music has amongst others artists: GMS, Tron, Chromatone, Soundaholix, Everblast, Wrecked Machines, KIM, DJ Mack, DJ Moon, Virtual Light

Cog and Flywheel came to fruition after years of study and perserverance. We played video game after video game, trying in vain to understand that truly vexing question, “Where the hell is that last heart piece”. Although we never found that elusive heart piece, in our searches we came to realize that the finest music composed in our time, nay, all time, can be found in video games. Having acquired this knowledge, we set out emulate the sonorous flute of the general MIDI soundset, the beautiful burst of white noise that is the 4-bit snare drum, using robots. Designed around a base-12 mathematical system, two advanced machines were born, and a molded-plastic era of music ushered into our age. Lolight Records is proud to present Cog and Flywheel.

Hailing from the golden south coast sands of Bournemouth bay, Mr G is the co-founder of emerging underground house label Forbidden Fruit. 

His journey into music addiction began in the mid 90s through the collection and trade of Old skool Rave, Drum and Bass & Techno tape packs at  the back of the school bus!  Since those days of innocent curiosity, Mr G has continued to fuel his habit through through well over a decade's collection of genre bending beats, harnessing any opportunity to unleash them upon willing dancefloors accross the globe. 

Having honed his trade with vinyl, he now runs a largely digital setup, spinning all things house & techno, championing the underground energetic grooves inspired through a life spent discovering the best dancefloors our world has to offer.

A born performer with an infectious energy, Mr G is most at home stirring up a storm on either side of the DJ booth, a true chameleon of the dance music scene.

One cold Saturday in 2007, two likeminded personalities decided to combine forces by sticking their heads together to create a track after both having operated solo for over a decade. From that moment, Audiowomb was born.

What started off as a musical try-out, developed rapidly into a concept, a dj team, and above all: a friendship between two musicians.

‘We complement each other very well. Our individual skills and focus, combined with our mutual experience in both mixing and producing, quickly emerged as a powerful combination,' Sten says. ‘From that point on we decided to create all our music under the Audiowomb moniker. Shortly after came the decision to team up as dj's as well.'

Due to their shared passion for deep, raw and hypnotizing sounds, they always strive to integrate that specific ‘Audiowomb sound’ in both their dj sets and their productions.
‘One cannot translate these elements into words,' Jeroen claims. ‘Music is emotion, a gut feeling. A track either has ‘it’, or not.’

'Technological development pushes the growth and progression of the electronic music industry fast forward and has already formed a wide range of different styles and genres. It keeps this music scene dynamic and interesting. We play and create music for the dance floor, without wandering off from our own path. We just want to make people dance: nothing more, nothing less.’

Audiowomb performed alongside: Sasha Carassi, Marco Bailey, Oscar Mulero, Knobs, Steve Rachmad, Pig & Dan, Egbert, Luetzenkirchen, Anton Pieete, Mike Wall, Tom Hades, and many others.

Audiowomb performed at: Studio 80 Amsterdam, Undercurrent - Amsterdam, Chicago Social Club - Amsterdam, Korsakoff - Amsterdam, Boom Chicago - Amsterdam, TWSTd – Amsterdam, Mp3 Live – Amsterdam, Perron - Rotterdam, Catwalk – Rotterdam, Bootleg DJ Café – Rotterdam, Victorie - Alkmaar, Tivoli de Helling - Utrecht, Dock 154 – Utrecht, ACU – Utrecht, Luxor Live - Arnhem, Club Purple – Arnhem, Klup - Groningen, Talent Factory – Den Bosch, De Boulevard – Breda, Fenix – Sittard, Estrado – Harderwijk, Kunstkeller - Giessen (DE), Reitercasino - Herborn (DE), The Corner Shop - London (UK), and many other venues.

***********************************************
"ADAPTRONIX" abgeleited von Adaptronik 
***********************************************
Adaptronik ist eine interdisziplinäre Wissenschaft, die sich mit dem Aufbau adaptiver (selbstanpassender) Systeme befasst. Die in der Adaptronik verwendeten Aktoren werden anders als in der Mechatronik in den Kraftfluss integriert und nutzen die elastomechanischen Eigenschaften der verwendeten Materialien aus. Ein Großteil der dafür eingesetzten Werkstoffe kann sowohl als Aktor als auch als Sensor verwendet werden. Die Materialien wandeln elektrische, thermische und magnetische Energie in mechanische Energie um und können ebenso den umgekehrten Prozess vollziehen. So reagieren die aktiven Werkstoffe auf Verformungen, Schwingungen und Lärm.

Very few new imprints have received such a warm welcome from all sides of the spectrum than Room With A View. Respected dj’s, worldwide music media & retailers have all been deeply impressed by the quality & vision transported by the label founded in spring 2009 by Dairmount & Anja Knupper in Hamburg. The label’s ethic is aiming to get back to timeless “emotional content” club music with a futuristic flair, while breaking the pattern of “functionality” that club music too often slips into these days. Room With A View presents a subtle mixture of House & Techno with a twist of freshness & Detroit influences. 

It is quite a little performance to invite a large range of dj’s to enjoy the same sound these days : Techno mammoths such as Carl Craig, Laurent Garnier, Ritchie Hawtin, Dubfire or Dj Hell, Deep House heavyweights such as Jimpster, Dj Deep, Manuel Tur or Brothers Vibe, Tech House masters such as Steve Bug, MANDY or Joris Voorn, Leftfield wizards such as Lawrence, Peter Kruder, Jazzanova or dj legends such as Danny Krivit or Francois K have all embraced the sound of the label with real enthusiasm…

A software engineer for about 16 years, at the age of 13 became involved with Electronic Music.

From 2003 to 2004, living in Gelsenkirchen, Germany, working in his main area (software engineering), he decided to shift his routine and began Deejaying in some local places, and other German clubs of the NRW state.

A staple in the Bay Area for years, lady DJ Zita has been steadily building a DJ queendom beat by beat. Known as a party rocker, classic record provider, tireless promoter and meticulous organizer, Zita has brought her sisterhood sounds to dancefloors on both coasts and overseas since 1999. Her captivating sound spans the eras and blends genres of body-rockin' music; she'll seamlessly segue from boombox classic hip hop to mothership trunk funk, spin smooth R&B treats along with timeless soul heroines and heroes, flip reggae dancehall riddims, throwback to '80s pop freestyle, and groove the dancefloor with her soulful deep house. At first one of only a handful of women on the scene, Zita established Bay Area Sistah Sound (BASS) to unite women DJs and performers. She can also be found most weekends holding down residencies in San Francisco and Oakland as part of DJ duo Golden Soundscapes with partner Dmadness, as well as producing fresh events spotlighting women in hip hop and guesting at many premier music nights and venues. With her dazzling style, fierce determination, and golden touch on the wheels, DJ Zita has changed the landscape and continues to shine.

After an extended hiatus, Blackchords are back and have been busy writing material for their third album ‘Shadows’. Forming in Melbourne, Blackchords quickly made a name for themselves when their 'chilling yet beautiful' music video ‘Broken Bones’ won Best Music Video in the prestigious St Kilda Film Festival.
Blackchords released their self-titled debut album through independent Melbourne label DustDevil Music, receiving widespread critical acclaim and rave reviews: “Melbourne quartet shoots for the stars on widescreen debut” (Rolling Stone). The album was shortlisted for The Australian Music Prize.
Songs from the debut album have been featured in the Australian television shows Underbelly: Razor, Offspring, Rescue Special Ops, Cops L.A.C. and international television including Teen Mom (MTV) and Being Human (NBC).
After extensive national touring, the band travelled to France and the UK, playing The Great Escape and Liverpool Sound City festivals. The music video for the band's second single ‘At World's End’ received airtime on MTV UK and NME TV. 
After returning to Australia, Blackchords accepted an invitation to open for Australian rock icons Powderfinger for the 'Sunset Sounds Farewell Tour' at Melbourne’s Sidney Myer Music Bowl. Blackchords went on to write and record the title track ‘As Night Falls’ for the Australian feature film ‘Blame’.
After a successful crowdfunding campaign, the band embarked on their sophomore album ‘A Thin Line’, working with Mercury Music Prize-nominated and Grammy Award-winning producer David Odlum (Glen Hansard, Tinariwen), releasing the album through ABC Music. As well as touring nationally, the band embarked on a tour of the USA and Canada, including performances at Austin's SXSW festival.
Through their relationship with music publisher Native Tongue, Blackchords continues to gain and maintain international exposure through features in acclaimed and popular television, such as Orange is the New Black (Netflix), Suits (UCP), Betrayal(ABC), Teen Wolf (MTV), Being Human (BBC), Shameless (Showtime) and more.

Started Dj-ing in 80s at indie gigs and then on pirate radio/tv station Network 21. Opened his first club in 1985, Toured as DJ with The Shamen, then signed with Rising High Records for the albums Flying High, Global Chillage. Joined up with Pete Namlook to record two albums as Dreamfish. Did two sessions for BBC's John Peel. Residencies at underground clubs like Lost and Megatripolis. Remixed Coldcut's Autumn Leaves which went on to become a classic. Played at Love Parade and Glastonbury festival throughout the 90s. 

Wrote for NME, Mixmag and i-D magazine, presented The Chill Out Zone on Kiss FM.Toured Europe, USA and Japan repeatedly, made mix CDs like The Morning After, Abstract Funk Theory, God Bless The Chilled. Signed with Ninja Tunes and made the album Its Tomorrow Already and singles Nepalese Bliss & Fish Dances. Got involved with the Big Chill at the very beginning in 1994 and played every year since for them. Appeared in the cult movie Modulations. Recorded an album in Japan with Jonah Sharp and Harry Hosono of YMO. Made a TV commercial, soundtracked a play on Radio 3 and remixed the Dr Who theme for the BBC. Talked about Brian Eno on C4. Moved his Nubient club to Big Chill Bar. Won Ibiza Chillout DJ of the year - twice. Did two mixes for Rob da Banks show on Radio 1. Remixed Anne Garner and 6th Sense. Made an Altermodern podcast for the Tate Britain.  2010 won Best Downtempo DJ again, and started new job running Apollo label as part of R+S...

Patrick DSP has been smashing sound systems around the world for several decades on three decks. Starting in his native Canada and finally landing himself in Berlin, where he currently resides. Beginning his campaign or techno in the mid 90s in Toronto, soon delved into the production side of things, and eventually mastering.

A quick study in the technical realm, the fast found himself working with renowned labels such as Kneâ€™ Deep Records and DJAX Up Beats, providing mastering, production and remixes for various labels, all the while building his repertoire or twisted pristine sounds.

In between jumping from Canada, to Brazil, to Berlin, Patrick managed to expand his abilities, not only making music from film scores to blistering techno, but also using his mastery of production to teach others their way around a studio, giving classes and lectures around the world. Never one to rest on his laurels, he was also performing across Europe, South America and North America, spreading his techno sound from intimate local clubs to festivals such as the Love Parade in Germany, ADE, MayDay, Awakenings, Fabrik, Tresor and many more.

His musical skills, along with his diverse range of technical ability, have not only resulted in an impressive discography of international releases, but have also allowed him to collaborate with some of the most talented names in techno, earning him the reputation of a true techno stalwart.

Hvoya aka Irina Kustovska got her first musical lessons at the age of 3 years old when her parents (professional pianists) began to foster love for the music in their child.
After having got classical music education, Hvoya started her independent electronica career in 2007. As a result of her creative work, an unusual mix of a vibrant feminine vocal, refined idm-beats and romantic acoustic melodies has been appeared. During the last two years Hvoya has got on well in recording collab album with Ukrainian chill-out project Zymosis (released on Sunline Rec., USA), producing several tracks with Jukeen in Slovenia and Portuguese project Hexagon Heaven (Francisco Godikinho), taking part in several big events (including International Firework Festival 2008). In February, 2009, Hvoya released her first solo album "Flower". A debut "plate" was released on "I, Absentee" experimental music label in the USA.
At the present time Hvoya works on her 2-nd album 'Veil'. New sound of her tracks could be described as "Intelligent Lounge Music (ILM)". It is a charismatic and romantic down-tempo tinged with bright palette of harmonies and refined noizzy sounds accompanied by Hvoya's velvet vocal. Experimenting with a new sound, the singer started cooperation with a famous Ukranian dj and producer Alexander Minikin (Kievbass/Ottosiderspunk). The new album is expected to be finished in April 2009.

Coordinated from Berlin, the netlabel CRAZY LANGUAGE was founded by AXIOM and HURON in 2006. Ever since Crazy Language has been serving as music filter and platform for artistic self-realisation. The label offers all experimental electronic music genres an outlet, for example IDM, Electronica, Glitch, Abstract, Ambient, Downbeat and Breaks. This is reflected in the passion of the netlabel owners as well as in the diversity of the music scene. With lots of love for music, Crazy Language is articulating itself in a dialect spoken all around the world by artists and music lovers alike: the Crazy Language of course.

The project Mathon has its name from a beautiful place in the Swiss Alps. Every year since 2003 Thomas Augustiny, Roger Stucki and Pete Leuenberg meet there and invite different musicians, to translate the impressive surrounding into music. The conceptual project is ambient music by its original definition: space becomes sound and sound generates space. This way four albums have been recorded, together with Ronny Spiegel, Maria Capelli, Nocolas Kellner and Maurice de Martin. The growing interest for the visualisation of the music, lead to installation for Etoy, HKB or the museum for communication. The pieces of the current release were remixed by international known musicians like; Kenneth Kirschner, i8u, SteinbrÃ¼chel or Digitalis.

Throcke is the creation of Christopher Mollineaux Carson. It is a solo studio project involving electronic and organic elements - distorted organs, cascading drums and soothing guitar melodies as well as quirky clicks and blurps. Occasionally there are layers of vocals, or perhaps a windy wash of rain. Throcke works such disparate textures into complex, melodic grooves to craft a truly original sound. The results are both accessible and constantly surprising.
Throcke self-produced his debut EP Advance Longing in 2005, followed by a string of single tracks. He then slowed down the songwriting for a few years while playing drums for the band UMAMI. 2009 marks his return, with the full-length album Sometimes Not Unpointful.
